BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:2026 Quarterly Cross-Group Learning Review & Sharing Meeting｜202
 6季度跨小组学习回顾与成果分享会议
DTSTART;TZID=GMT 标准时间:20260702T130000
DTEND;TZID=GMT 标准时间:20260702T163000
CLASS:PUBLIC
DESCRIPTION:Dear D Talent Team\,\n\n尊敬的 D Talent 团队，\n\n \n\nW
 e are pleased to invite you to our 2026 Quarterly Cross-Group Learning Rev
 iew & Sharing Meeting. 🎉\n\n我们诚挚地邀请您参加2026 年度
 季度跨小组学习回顾与成果分享会议。\n\n \n\nThis quarterly
  meeting is designed to enhance learning communication and collaboration a
 cross different groups. The session will focus on reviewing the progress o
 f ongoing training programs\, sharing learning outcomes\, and aligning on 
 learning priorities and course content for the upcoming quarter.\n\n本次
 季度会议旨在加强不同小组之间的学习沟通与协作，重
 点回顾当前培训项目的整体进展，分享学习成果，并对
 齐下一阶段的学习重点与课程内容。\n\n \n\n*  👥Participan
 ts / 参与人员：\n\n*  All D Talent Program group members are required
  to attend.\n\n*  D Talent Program 小组成员需必须参加。\n\n*  Ma
 nagement level members are welcome to attend on an optional basis.\n\n*  
 管理层可自愿参加。\n\n \n\nDuring the meeting\, we will:\n\n会
 议将主要包括以下内容：\n\n \n\n*  🗂️Review Coursera accoun
 t usage and accumulated training hours across groups\n\n  回顾各小组 
 Coursera 账户使用情况及培训时长\n\n*  🌟Share key learning ou
 tcomes\, application cases\, and achievements from different groups\n\n   
  分享各小组的学习成果、实践应用案例及阶段性成果\n\n
 *  🧭Align on upcoming learning tasks\, priorities\, and course content 
 for the next quarter\n\n    对齐下一季度的学习任务、重点方
 向及课程规划\n\n*  💡Collect feedback and suggestions to continuou
 sly improve our group learning initiatives\n\n    收集反馈与建议，
 持续优化小组学习机制\n\n \n\nThis meeting will serve as an impor
 tant platform for cross-group knowledge sharing and mutual learning. We lo
 ok forward to your participation and valuable insights.\n\n本次会议将
 作为跨小组知识共享与经验交流的重要平台，期待您的
 积极参与和宝贵建议。\n\n \n\nThank you\, and we look forward to 
 seeing you at the meeting.\n\n感谢您的支持，期待您的参与！
 😊\n\n \n\nBest regards\,\n\nLily Liu is sending this email on behalf of
  the cross-functional project team.\n\n \n\n______________________________
 __________________________________________________\n\nMicrosoft Teams meet
 ing \n\nJoin: https://teams.microsoft.com/meet/383016132007181?p=6rsQ0tp6w
 AUcWb4Pt2 <https://teams.microsoft.com/meet/383016132007181?p=6rsQ0tp6wAUc
 Wb4Pt2>  \n\nMeeting ID: 383 016 132 007 181 \n\nPasscode: 59jX7Zx3 \n\n__
 ______________________________\n\nNeed help? <https://aka.ms/JoinTeamsMeet
 ing?omkt=en-US>  | System reference <https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-
 join/19%3ameeting_MWM4YTU5NTQtYjk5ZS00MDMzLWIzY2MtNjI4ZWEwZjFlMGQx%40threa
 d.v2/0?context=%7b%22Tid%22%3a%2249bcf5a3-8181-4f6c-aa5a-2625c7e55082%22%2
 c%22Oid%22%3a%2219e4d4bd-ed8a-42c2-9001-77c414b89798%22%7d>  \n\nFor organ
 izers: Meeting options <https://teams.microsoft.com/meetingOptions/?organi
 zerId=19e4d4bd-ed8a-42c2-9001-77c414b89798&tenantId=49bcf5a3-8181-4f6c-aa5
 a-2625c7e55082&threadId=19_meeting_MWM4YTU5NTQtYjk5ZS00MDMzLWIzY2MtNjI4ZWE
 wZjFlMGQx@thread.v2&messageId=0&language=en-US>  \n\nPrivacy and security 
 <https://filehub.admiralcloud.com/dl/5/6501531f-d1ca-436b-832a-1d684ab9ad7
